The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, July 16, 2004  Business Briefs																								 New Delhi, July 15: The government today said there is no plan to merge telecom PSUs BSNL and MTNL. There is no proposal to merge BSNL and MTNL, Shakeel Ahmad, minister of state for communications and IT, told Rajya Sabha in a written reply. To another query, he said the government had not incurred any revenue loss in the VSNL-Tata selloff deal. 																								 New Delhi, July 15: The directorate general of civil aviation has told the administrative ministry that the decision to reduce the age of aircraft on lease from 15 to seven years would not be feasible as it would have a massive financial impact on most of the carriers.																								 London, July 15: Opec today agreed to raise its daily production target by 500,000 barrels, or 2 per cent, from August 1 in an effort to keep crude prices from lurching higher. The price of oil is stuck above $40 a barrel.																								 Mumbai, July 15: The board of Alembic Glass Industries will consider a proposal to issue preferential equity shares to promoter group companies at its meeting scheduled on July 19.																								 Calcutta, July 15: AirTel has launched the 012 Plan for its prepaid customers. It has also re-framed recharge coupon values to add to the talktime value.
